I am a nationally ranked chess player and I welcome you to learn the game. No experience is needed.  I will include my experience at the bottom of this description.

•How to read the chess board and understand what the numbers and letters mean on it
•The movements, significance, and orientation of all of the pieces
•Fundamental rules of orienting one’s pieces, the start of the game, and player etiquettes 
•How to win the game: what it means to “check” your opponent or “checkmate” your opponent, etc.
•Examples of each concept
•Mini-games that exercise different concepts 

The next sequences are TBA!

description:
TextUp—Social Good Software Company—Seeking Software Design Intern(s)

TextUp is a software business that was developed throughout our founders’ recent time as Brown and RISD undergrads. Our software is designed to address the needs of social work agencies and nonprofits at a price that they can afford. Our business has recently grown to have customers throughout the east coast and we were the first ever student-run business to win the RI Business Plan Competition.

While design expertise is a must, we’re particularly looking for students interested in the intersection of software and social good. Our interns will work closely with our founders and have exposure to the ins and outs of starting and running a tech company.

Required Skills: As we add additional functionality to TextUp, we're looking for someone with a keen eye for intuitive design to help us ensure TextUp is user-friendly. This intern will work closely with our Lead Designer to create user interface designs. They will garner feedback on those designs from TextUp users and integrate their feedback into a final mock-up, which will be implemented by our coding team. Prior experience in software design is a must.   

Start Date: Flexible. Late fall semester or spring semester.

Payment: $20/hour, potential for higher wage for aptly experienced candidates  

Perks: We’re willing to help the intern(s) apply for course credit where applicable. There is high likelihood that this could evolve into a paid summer internship or potentially a full-time salaried position and company equity. 

Email your résumé to connect@textup.org and we'll follow up to schedule an interview. Candidates reviewed on a rolling basis.
title: Software Design Internship
